File: ANC spokesperson Pule Mabe returns to his office. JOHANNESBURG - ANC National spokesperson Pule Mabe says the governing party will not comment at this point on allegations made at the state capture inquiry. On Monday, former President Jacob Zuma told the commission that former Mineral Resources Minister, Ngoako Ramatlhodi was an apartheid government spy. WATCH: Zuma drops names, makes huge claims at state capture inquiry "It is important that we allow the process of the commission to proceed unhindered," Mabe said. The party says it’s encouraging to see its members have heeded the call to testify. Mabe says the ANC is willing to testify before the commission if called.